	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 7th 1:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Praetor!<br><br>I was recently reviewing your Damage Calculation Guide you posted a while back. Interesting work! I went through the calculations and came up with some eye-opening realizations.&nbsp;&nbsp; One was not so surprising, as I had surmised it in combat, that being that my Mithril 2-hand sword was better than my Wurmslayer. The other was very surprising!  This assumes, of course, that I punched the calculator correctly, and I make NO GUARANTEE that I did so!  (I have a Geology Degree...)  <br><br>This is what I came up with and then I have a question or two.  Keep in mind I am a 49th lvl Paladin with 130 strength. My Weapon skills are maxed at 200 and my main three weapons are: <br><br>A Mithril Two-Hand Sword: Dam 21, Dly 40, 31% haste<br>Note: Mithril has an effective delay of about 31<br>Wurmslayer: Dam 25, Dly 40<br>Dwarven Sap: Dam 8, Dly 20<br><br>My 1-hand level Bonus is: 8     (Level – 25)/3<br>My 2-hand level Bonus is: 13.3  (Level – 25)/1.8<br><br>Max Damage for my weapons:<br>Equation: (( Weapon Skill+Str)/100)*(Weapon Damage+Lvl Bonus)<br>For the Mithril 2-hand sword this equation looks like this:<br><br>((200 + 130)/100) * (21 + 13.3) = 113 (rounded)<br><br>Assuming I did that correctly, my max for my weapons looks like this:<br><br>Mithril: 113<br>Wurm:	108.9<br>SAP:	52.8<br><br>Magic Numbers are: <br>(by the way, the realization of a “magic number” only confirmed what I was seeing in combat! It was nice to have a name put to it!)  <br>Equation: 2 * Weapon Dam + Level Bonus<br><br>Mithril: 55   (2 * 21) + 13.3<br>Wurm:	58    (2 * 25) + 8<br>SAP:	24    (2 * 8) + 8<br><br>Okay, now for Minimum Damage! (This was a bit of an eye-opener)<br>Equation: 1+1hand level bonus OR 3 + 2hand level bonus<br><br>Mithril: 16    (3 + 13.3)=16.3  (2-hand)<br>Wurm:	9      (1 + 8)=9  (1-hand)<br>SAP:	9      (1 + 8)=9  (1-hand)<br><br>Yes, that’s right, my MINIMUM IS THE SAME FOR MY SAP AND MY WURM and my minimum is MUCH higher for my Mithril 2-hand sword!<br><br>Now for Average Damages<br>Equation: (.45*Min)+(.45*Magic Number)+(.1*Max)<br><br>Mithril: 43.25   (.45*16)+(.45*55)+(.1*113)<br>Wurm: 40.95<br>SAP:  20.13<br><br>Double Attack Formula:  (Skill + Level)/500<br><br>(200 + 49)/500 = 0.498<br><br>And now the BIG Test!! Damage per Second!! WOOT!!<br>Equation: Accuracy% * (Ave Dam/(Dly/10))*(1+Double Attack%)<br><br>Mithril: 13.58  (.65*(43.25/(31/10)))*(1+0.498)<br>Note: 31 Delay = Effective Delay after Haste<br><br>Wurm:	9.97    (.65*(40.95/(40/10)))*(1+0.498)<br>SAP:	9.8     (.65*(19.75/(20/10)))*(1+0.498)<br><br>YEP, you see that right. My SAP has almost the same Damage per Second as my WURMSLAYER!!  And the Mithril beats them both handily.  I realize that with 1-hs and 1-hb weapons you get to add AC from a shield and get to add Bash damage during a battle.<br><br>So why does the SAP keep up with the Wurm?  Because the Wurmslayer is just too SLOW!! With the SAP, you apply that level bonus MUCH more frequently than you do with the Wurm and it really adds up!<br><br>QUESTIONS:<br><br>What about the 2-hs Damage Bonus for 2-handed weapons with delays of 40 or higher?  No mention of that. I know it’s kinda new, so how would that figure in? That will only make the Mithril 2-hand sword even BETTER!!<br><br>Also, the EQPrices Website shows different Damage per Second valuations for these weapons than what I came up with. Not to say they are right, but just as an FYI.  I have a feeling EQPrices didn't take into account the Mithril Haste for their DPS but I don't know why the Wurm is so high.  EQPrices shows DPS as:<br><br>Mithril: 10.75<br>Wurm:    12.75<br>SAP:     8.5<br><br>This would give the impression that the Wurmslayer was the better weapon, when my calculations show the exact opposite and I firmly believe my Mithril 2-hander is a better weapon than my Wurm as far as pure damage output. As a matter of fact, my calculations show my SAP to be about as effective as the Wurm.<br><br>Thanks for the interesting post! Anxiously awaiting your response!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>49th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>“Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness”<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
