	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 8th 1:29 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wow, I forgot all about that post..<br><br>I redid all the numbers for you, and it looks like you did everything correctly.<br><br>For the two handed damage bonuses dependant upon delay, I haven't found anything really <i>solid</i> on how to calculate the exact damage bonus anymore.&nbsp;&nbsp;As far as I can tell, two handed bonuses are calculated now something like this:<br><br>For delay less than 28:<br><br><i>{(level-25)/3}+1</i> (or, the one handed bonus +1)<br><br>For delay from 29-39:<br><br><i>{(level-25)/3}+{(level-27)/4}</i><br><br>For delay from 40-42;<br><br><i>{(level-25)/3}+{(level-27)/4}+1</i><br><br>For delay from 43 and up:<br><br><i>{(level-25)/3}+{(level-27)/4}+1+{(WeaponDelay-34)/3}</i><br><br>Have I lost you yet? :)<br><br>Since these calculations get just <i>slightly hard</i>(*cough*), I gave up doing them manually and just started using <a href=HTTP://www.geocities.com/copelandeq/weaponanalyzer.html target=_new>Copeland's Weapon Analyzer</a>.  Bear in mind that these formulae and program are only reasonably accurate against blue con NPCs.  Once you get into red con fights, all this conventional damage calculation gets thrown out the window, and I can't even <i>begin</i> to try and explain that without some more logs.<br><br>If you want to discover more than I've presented, by all means find yourself a good log parser and /log on when you're fighting in experience groups.  A lot of it is really eye-opening stuff (such as why a 13/20 weapon outdamages a 33/35 weapon on red con mobs).<br><br>Anyways, never quit trying to learn new things about this game!  It's absolutely shocking some of what you'll uncover.<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Praetor</b>, 60th Crusader<br>Avatars of Discord</td></tr>
